# Citation metadata. GitHub renders a "Cite this repository" widget from this
# file. Format: https://citation-file-format.github.io/
#
# Validate before pushing:
#   pip install cffconvert && cffconvert --validate
# or with `pre-commit` hook `python-jsonschema/check-jsonschema --schemafile <CFF schema>`.

cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use SOCIA in your teaching, your research or any derived work,
  please cite it using the metadata in this file.

title: "SOCIA — Plataforma para el entrenamiento de gestión de incidentes de Ciberseguridad tutorizada con Inteligencia Artificial"

abstract: >-
  SOCIA is an open-source platform that lets vocational-training students
  resolve realistic Security Operations Centre (SOC) cases against actual
  tooling (TheHive, Graylog, OPNsense, Wazuh, Velociraptor, Malcolm). It
  records the student's actions, verifies progress automatically by matching
  HTTP network signatures against pedagogical milestones, offers progressive
  AI-tutored hints and produces a final evaluation PDF. It supports a
  standalone mode (a student loads a workflow.json locally) and a managed
  mode (a teacher launches cases for a class from a self-hosted server with
  a web admin panel). The project is led by IES Rafael Alberti (Cádiz) in
  collaboration with CIFP N.º 1 Cuenca and Aktios Security Services, and is
  funded by the Spanish Ministry of Education, Vocational Training and
  Sports under the Recovery, Transformation and Resilience Plan (PRTR) /
  NextGenerationEU.

type: software

# Authors are the collaborating institutions. CFF distinguishes "entity"
# authors (organisations) from "person" authors by the use of `name` instead
# of `given-names`/`family-names`. The order matters: IES Rafael Alberti is
# the coordinating centre and is listed first. Individual contributors who
# want to be cited by name can be added before/between/after the entity
# entries — citation tools render the list in order.
authors:
  - name: "IES Rafael Alberti"
    city: "Cádiz"
    country: ES
    website: "https://iesrafaelalberti.es"
  - name: "CIFP N.º 1 Cuenca"
    city: "Cuenca"
    country: ES
    website: "https://www.cifpcuenca.es"
  - name: "Aktios Security Services, S.L."
    country: ES
    website: "https://www.aktios.com"

repository-code: "https://github.com/IES-Rafael-Alberti/socia"
url: "https://socia.fpciberseguridad.com"

license: MIT

keywords:
  - cybersecurity
  - security operations center
  - SOC
  - incident response
  - vocational education
  - educational technology
  - AI tutoring
  - large language models
  - llm-as-judge
  - automated assessment
  - browser extension
  - network forensics
  - digital forensics

# Update on each tagged release (pnpm version <…> + git tag).
version: "1.0.0"
# date-released: 2026-XX-XX   # uncomment and fill on first public release

# When the project is archived to Zenodo to obtain a DOI, add it here. The
# Zenodo–GitHub integration produces a DOI per release; pick the
# "concept DOI" (cross-version) for general citation.
# identifiers:
#   - type: doi
#     value: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"
#     description: "Concept DOI (all versions)"

# If you publish a paper or thesis describing SOCIA, point to it as the
# preferred citation so academic citation tools surface the paper instead
# of the software metadata.
